Document: VisualShaderNodeVec2Constant  
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodevec2constant.rst  
Summary: Class representing a constant Vec2 node in the Visual Shader graph.  

Inherits: VisualShaderNode < ShaderNode < Reference < Object  

A VisualShaderNodeVec2Constant is used to define a constant 2D vector (Vec2) value within a Visual Shader. It provides a fixed value that can be connected to other nodes in the shader graph. This node is useful for setting static positions, sizes, or other Vec2-based parameters that do not change during runtime.  

The node's value is specified through its properties and can be adjusted via the editor's inspector panel. When used in a shader, the constant value is directly embedded into the generated shader code, ensuring consistent behavior across all instances of the shader.  

Key Rule: This node is specifically designed for static Vec2 values and cannot be used for dynamic calculations or inputs that require runtime variability.
